A helicopter crashed into the ocean just off Miami Beach on Saturday afternoon, cops said. The splashdown occurred at around 1:10 p.m. near 10th St., Miami Beach police said. Video posted by the police department shows the small aircraft descending rapidly as beachgoers enjoyed the surf and sun. No casualties were reported. Two occupants of the helicopter were transported in stable condition to Jackson Memorial Hospital, police said. The Federal Aviation Administration has responded to the scene. Itâ€™s unclear what caused the crash. Police closed a portion of the beach as authorities investigate the incident.